  "text": "Transient transfection and cDNA constructs. FcFGFR1 pEF-BOS constructs have been previously described [CITATION_1] . Human full-length FGFR1WT pcDNA3.1 was provided by Pamela Maher (Department of Cell Biology, The Scripps Research Institute, La Jolla, CA). Mouse STAT3 pZeoSV2 was provided by Valeria Poli (Molecular Biotechnology Center, University of Turin, Turin, Italy). Point mutations in FGFR1 Y677F, STAT3, and R609L constructs were obtained by QuickChange site-directed mutagenesis (Stratagene) and were confirmed by DNA sequencing. NH 2 -terminal myctagged-JAK2 constructs were made by Gateway cloning (Invitrogen) according to the instructions of the manufacturer. Short interfering RNA (siRNA) ON-TARGET oligonucleotides against FGFR2 were purchased from Thermo Fisher Scientific. C-Src and Jak2 siRNA were purchased from Santa Cruz Biotechnology. Nontargeting control siRNA were purchased from Qiagen. Gene Juice reagent (Novagen, MERCK Bioscience) and DharmaFECT3 (Dharmacon) were used according to the instructions of the manufacturer.",
